      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Minimum wage hikes in small towns with low cost of living can be a double-edged sword. On one hand, they can help workers earn a living wage, boosting local spending and potentially increasing business. On the other hand, they can strain small businesses that operate on thin margins, possibly forcing them to raise prices or cut jobs. It's a delicate balance, and the impact varies based on local economic conditions.",
